This is a hilariously upscaled howitzer-type primary weapon for your slightly-bigger-than-huge future war robot.

Note that this is just the weapon. The turntable to actually mount it on your robot is not included, but is available for free on my profile.

Despite how it looks, the threading on the barrel and the accelerator coils both are actually designed to print in one piece and be self-supporting when elevated to about 30 degrees or so. Just make sure the rails, piston rods and the actual body of the gun are suitably supported to prevent warping and you should be good to go.

This is an enormous two-bladed close combat saw weapon for huge battle robots. It comes in four pieces - the actual saw part, an elbow joint, an upper arm piece, and the shoulder joint. You can simply superglue the parts together to achieve the handedness and posing you wish. The shoulder joint has a built-in half-socket for a 5mm disc magnet, and the saw is essentially symmetrical so it'll look just as good as a left or right arm (though you may want to keep which side you'll want to use it for in mind while you're planning your supports). The arm can be built as either a left or right arm.

As this is based on a handful of different (free) sources, I'm offering it for free:

The saw blade itself is from the Armor Bearer Saw by Arajar: https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3989916

And the actual arm is 40K Big Reaper Titan AT Style Chainfist by The_Titan_Manufactorium: https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/40k-big-reaper-titan-at-style-chainfist

Thank you for the awesome models!

This is an enormous heavy energy weapon arm for huge battle robots. The elbow joint has a well for a 5mm magnet in it, along with interface ports to make it compatible with the WB series of slightly-bigger-than-huge battle robots.

Edit 4/21/22: The original Heavy Turbo Cannon was kind of a chonky lad. I made an upgraded 'Slim' version, essentially scaling it down by 15%, then extending the barrel and rejiggering the mounts to fit it again - giving it a lighter, sleeker form factor, while still remaining a giant fuckoff cannon. I also smoothed out some of the geometry to give the main chassis a more rounded look.

I also went and smoothed out the geometry on the original one while I was at it - both are included in this download, the original being the 'Big Smoothed' version, while the newer lighter model is the 'Slim' version. Enjoy!

Fixed a geometry error with the trim on the model, uploaded as the 'Fix' versions. Sorry for the inconvenience.

The elbow joint has a well for a 5mm magnet in it, along with interface ports to make it compatible with the WB series of slightly-bigger-than-huge battle robots. Note that the weapon isn't symmetrical, so if you want a matching pair you'll need to mirror one.

This is a generic upper arm piece compatible with my RV-A series of guns. It's based on a model I found floating around on the internet - unfortunately I can't find the creator, but kudos to whoever made it - with a few modifications, so here it is for free for convenience's sake.

There are five variants, choose whichever fits your purposes:

RV Arm is the original model as-is.
RV Arm Elbow Magnet has a magnet well for a 5x1mm disc magnet cut into the lower end of the arm.
RV Arm Shoulder Magnet cuts the ball joint for the shoulder in half and adds a half-socket for a 5mm disc magnet to the top surface.
RV Arm Double Magnet has both the elbow magnet well and the shoulder half-socket.
Finally, the RV Arm Plug has a shoulder half-socket and a slightly-less-than-5mm diameter plug built into the elbow surface that'll fit into the magnet well of my RV-A series of guns.

This is a two-barreled high energy weapon that'll fit perfectly on top of your gigantic future war robot.

This one is really just a quick kitbash I put together out of a few different free weapons I found floating around on the internet; therefore, I'm offering it for free. It does have some holes and weird geometry in it but it *does* slice and print without issues in Lychee at least. I'll make a fancier cleaner (paid) version with my own aesthetic at some point.
